<div class="col-md-12">
  <center><h3><strong>"//paprthin</strong>. <em>order. backout. and inventory."</em><h3></center>
</div>
<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= pie_chart Request.group(:created_at).count %>
    <p>Only <strong><%= link_to "Order", distributors_path %></strong> from the list of the items that you want. You can also see <strong><%= link_to "Past Orders", requests_path %></strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= pie_chart Backout.group(:item1).count %>
  <p>No inventory is complete without <strong><%= link_to "Backouts", backouts_path %></strong>. Make sure you count them right.<p>
</div>
<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= bar_chart Inventory.group(:name).count %>
  <p>Nobody likes doing <strong><%= link_to "Inventories", inventories_path %></strong>, but someone has to do it.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= bar_chart Post.group(:title).group(:created_at).count %>
  <p>Send in your <strong><%= link_to "Reports", posts_path %></h4></strong> here.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= pie_chart User.group(:username).count %>
  <p>See how many <strong><%= link_to "Users", users_path %></strong> have access to your app and their identities.</p>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
  <%= column_chart Good.group(:name).count %>
  <p>Add your <%= link_to "Products", new_good_path %></h4> here. You can view, edit or delete them too.</p>
</div>

